In this article, President Donald Trump proclaims October 6, 2017, as National Manufacturing Day in the United States. He praises American manufacturers and their workers for their contributions to the economy, national security, and innovation. Trump emphasizes the importance of the American entrepreneur and worker, highlighting their determination, work ethic, and ability to turn visions into reality. He also acknowledges the role of advanced technology in manufacturing and the job opportunities it creates. The article mentions the decline of American manufacturing due to government neglect, unfair trade deals, and high taxes, but Trump promises to address these issues and create a level playing field for American manufacturing. He concludes by calling upon all Americans to celebrate and support the entrepreneurs and workers in manufacturing.